1
00:00:01,302 --> 00:00:05,073
Sweetie Belle: OH, ARE YOU SURE
ABOUT THIS, SCOOTALOO?

2
00:00:05,106 --> 00:00:08,342
I'VE NEVER EVEN HEARD
OF A PONY ZIP-LINING BEFORE.

3
00:00:08,376 --> 00:00:09,510
NEITHER HAVE I,

4
00:00:09,543 --> 00:00:12,246
BUT SPIKE
TOLD ME IT WAS AWESOME!

5
00:00:20,621 --> 00:00:23,191
AAH!
AAH!
AAH!

6
00:00:23,224 --> 00:00:24,492
WHOA!

7
00:00:24,525 --> 00:00:25,826
OH!
WHOA!

8
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,628
[ ALL GROAN ]

9
00:00:27,661 --> 00:00:30,531
SEE ANYTHING?

10
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:36,437
TREE SAP AND PINE NEEDLES,
BUT NO CUTIE MARK.

11
00:00:36,470 --> 00:00:38,206
PLAN B?

12
00:00:38,239 --> 00:00:39,607
YEAH.

13
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:43,244
YOU KNOW WHERE WE CAN FIND
A CANNON AT THIS HOUR?

14
00:00:44,812 --> 00:00:46,314
IT'S NO USE.

15
00:00:46,347 --> 00:00:47,615
NO MATTER WHAT WE TRY,

16
00:00:47,648 --> 00:00:50,218
WE ALWAYS END UP
WITHOUT OUR CUTIE MARKS,

17
00:00:50,251 --> 00:00:53,687
AND, SURPRISINGLY OFTEN,
COVERED IN TREE SAP.

18
00:00:53,721 --> 00:00:56,357
MAYBE WE SHOULD DO SOMETHING
LESS DANGEROUS,

19
00:00:56,390 --> 00:00:57,491
LIKE PILLOW TESTING

20
00:00:57,525 --> 00:01:00,194
OR FLOWER SNIFFING.

21
00:01:00,228 --> 00:01:04,098
THIS TOWN IS FULL OF PONIES
WHO HAVE THEIR CUTIE MARKS.

22
00:01:04,132 --> 00:01:05,733
WHY DON'T WE ASK THEM
HOW THEY DID IT?

23
00:01:05,766 --> 00:01:08,436
THAT'S A GREAT,
SAFE IDEA.

24
00:01:08,469 --> 00:01:12,473
YEAH, AND WE CAN START WITH
THE COOLEST PONY IN PONYVILLE.

25
00:01:12,506 --> 00:01:14,508
APPLEJACK!
RARITY!

26
00:01:14,542 --> 00:01:17,511
COME ON, GUYS.
I SAID COOL.

27
00:01:17,545 --> 00:01:18,679
YOU KNOW
WHO I'M TALKING ABOUT.

28
00:01:18,712 --> 00:01:22,650
SHE'S FAST, SHE'S TOUGH,
SHE'S NOT AFRAID OF ANYTHING.

29
00:01:22,683 --> 00:01:24,785
PINKIE PIE?
PINKIE PIE?

30
00:01:24,818 --> 00:01:28,789
NO! THE GREATEST FLYER
EVER TO COME OUT OF CLOUDSDALE.

31
00:01:28,822 --> 00:01:30,391
FLUTTERSHY?
FLUTTERSHY?

32
00:01:30,424 --> 00:01:32,860
NO!
RAINBOW DASH!

33
00:01:32,893 --> 00:01:35,729
OH, YEAH,
THAT MAKES MUCH MORE SENSE.

34
00:01:35,763 --> 00:01:37,665
OF COURSE.
LET'S DO IT.

35
00:01:37,698 --> 00:01:40,234
LET'S FIND OUT HOW RAINBOW DASH
EARNED HER CUTIE MARK.

36
00:01:40,268 --> 00:01:41,335
YEAH!
YEAH!

37
00:01:41,369 --> 00:01:42,336
AH!

38
00:01:42,370 --> 00:01:43,671
AH! UNH!

39
00:01:43,704 --> 00:01:46,207
[ ALL GROAN ]

40
00:01:47,375 --> 00:01:49,643
* MY LITTLE PONY

41
00:01:49,677 --> 00:01:51,479
* MY LITTLE PONY

42
00:01:51,512 --> 00:01:53,414
* AH-AH-AH-AH

43
00:01:53,447 --> 00:01:55,483
* MY LITTLE PONY

44
00:01:55,516 --> 00:01:57,818
* I USED TO WONDER
WHAT FRIENDSHIP COULD BE *

45
00:01:57,851 --> 00:01:59,487
* MY LITTLE PONY

46
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:02,356
* UNTIL YOU ALL SHARED
THIS MAGIC WITH ME *

47
00:02:02,390 --> 00:02:04,425
* BIG ADVENTURE
* TONS OF FUN

48
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:06,560
* A BEAUTIFUL HEART
FAITHFUL AND STRONG *

49
00:02:06,594 --> 00:02:08,262
* SHARING KINDNESS
* IT'S AN EASY FEAT

50
00:02:08,296 --> 00:02:10,531
* AND MAGIC
MAKES IT ALL COMPLETE *

51
00:02:10,564 --> 00:02:12,800
* YEAH, MY LITTLE PONY

52
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:19,840
* DO YOU KNOW YOU'RE ALL
MY VERY BEST FRIENDS? *

53
00:02:24,878 --> 00:02:27,915
[ MOTOR REVVING ]

54
00:02:27,948 --> 00:02:29,383
[ CHITTERING ]

55
00:02:29,417 --> 00:02:30,451
[ GASPS ]

56
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:32,152
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

57
00:02:33,487 --> 00:02:35,956
Applejack: GET BACK HERE,
YOU THIEVIN' VARMINTS!

58
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:37,591
THIEVIN' WHAT, NOW?

59
00:02:37,625 --> 00:02:38,859
[ PANTING ]
[ ALL GASP ]

60
00:02:38,892 --> 00:02:40,428
WHOA!

61
00:02:40,461 --> 00:02:42,696
APPLE BLOOM?

62
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:46,867
HEY, SIS, HOW'D YOU GET
YOUR CUTIE MARK?

63
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,837
I NEVER TOLD YOU
THAT STORY?

64
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:52,606
HEY, I THOUGHT WE WERE
GONNA ASK RAINBOW DASH.

65
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:54,608
WE NEED ALL THE HELP
WE CAN GET.

66
00:02:54,642 --> 00:02:56,977
UGH! FINE.

67
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:59,947
WHY, SHOOT,
I WAS JUST A LITTLE FILLY --

68
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:02,216
EVEN LITTLER THAN Y'ALL.

69
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:05,553
I DIDN'T WANT TO SPEND MY LIFE
ON A MUDDY OLD APPLE FARM.

70
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:09,290
I WANTED TO LIVE
THE SOPHISTICATED LIFE,

71
00:03:09,323 --> 00:03:11,492
LIKE MY AUNT AND UNCLE ORANGE.

72
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:15,596
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

73
00:03:15,629 --> 00:03:19,700
SO I SET OUT TO TRY MY LUCK
IN THE BIG CITY -- MANEHATTAN --

74
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:23,571
THE MOST COSMOPOLITAN CITY
IN ALL OF EQUESTRIA.

75
00:03:23,604 --> 00:03:25,606
HEY, OUT OF THE WAY!

76
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:29,510
I KNEW I'D FIND OUT WHO I
WAS MEANT TO BE IN MANEHATTAN.

77
00:03:29,543 --> 00:03:31,545
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

78
00:03:34,948 --> 00:03:37,651
AUNT ORANGE, UNCLE ORANGE,

79
00:03:37,685 --> 00:03:40,321
THANK Y'ALL SO MUCH
FOR LETTING ME STAY.

80
00:03:40,354 --> 00:03:42,256
[ Posh accent ]
"Y'ALL." [ LAUGHS ]

81
00:03:42,290 --> 00:03:43,791
ISN'T SHE
JUST THE LIVING END?

82
00:03:43,824 --> 00:03:45,693
[ Posh accent ]
HOW QUAINT.

83
00:03:45,726 --> 00:03:47,828
DON'T WORRY,
WE'LL HAVE YOU ACTING

84
00:03:47,861 --> 00:03:50,298
LIKE A TRUE MANEHATTANITE
IN NO TIME.

85
00:03:50,331 --> 00:03:52,333
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

86
00:03:55,436 --> 00:03:58,406
AND HOW ARE YOU FINDING
GOOD OLD MANEHATTAN?

87
00:03:58,439 --> 00:04:00,007
[ Posh accent ]
OH, IT'S SIMPLY DIVINE.

88
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:02,543
VERY WELL SAID,
MY DEAR.

89
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:04,512
ALTHOUGH, I MUST ADMIT

90
00:04:04,545 --> 00:04:06,414
THE CITY NOISE
TOOK SOME GETTING USED TO.

91
00:04:06,447 --> 00:04:08,582
WHERE I'M FROM,
NIGHTS ARE SO QUIET,

92
00:04:08,616 --> 00:04:11,552
YOU SELDOM HEAR A PEEP
UNTIL THE ROOSTERS WAKE YOU.

93
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:12,620
THE WHAT?

94
00:04:12,653 --> 00:04:16,524
I SAY, MY DEAR, WHAT
IN THE WORLD IS A...ROOSTER?

95
00:04:16,557 --> 00:04:17,925
[ Thinking ]
WHAT'S HE TALKING ABOUT?

96
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:20,894
WHAT DO I SAY? I DON'T
WANT TO LOOK LIKE A FOOL.

97
00:04:20,928 --> 00:04:23,364
[ BELL DINGS ]
DINNER IS SERVED.

98
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:27,835
[ Normal voice ]
THANK GOODNESS.

99
00:04:27,868 --> 00:04:29,937
BEING A CITY PONY
IS HARD WORK.

100
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:31,672
I'M SO HUNGRY,
I COULD EAT A...

101
00:04:41,014 --> 00:04:43,551
COCK-A-DOODLE-DOO.

102
00:04:43,584 --> 00:04:46,987
OH, I WONDER WHAT GRANNY SMITH
AND BIG MACINTOSH ARE UP TO.

103
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:49,590
I'LL BET THEY'RE
APPLE-BUCKING THEIR WAY

104
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:51,825
THROUGH
THE RED DELICIOUS TREES.

105
00:04:51,859 --> 00:04:54,728
OH, WHAT I WOULDN'T GIVE
FOR JUST ONE BITE.

106
00:04:54,762 --> 00:04:58,666
I NEVER FELT SO HOMESICK IN ALL
MY DAYS AS I DID RIGHT THEN.

107
00:04:58,699 --> 00:05:00,701
[ BOOM! ]

108
00:05:00,734 --> 00:05:02,336
IT WAS AMAZING.

109
00:05:02,370 --> 00:05:05,973
A RAINBOW,
POINTING RIGHT BACK TO HOME.

110
00:05:06,006 --> 00:05:08,709
IN THAT MOMENT,
IT ALL BECAME CLEAR.

111
00:05:08,742 --> 00:05:11,879
I KNEW RIGHT THEN
JUST WHO I WAS SUPPOSED TO BE.

112
00:05:16,384 --> 00:05:17,951
[ TWINKLE! ]

113
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:19,887
THAT'S WHEN THIS HERE
APPEARED.

114
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:22,756
I'VE BEEN HAPPILY
WORKING THE FARM EVER SINCE.

115
00:05:22,790 --> 00:05:25,659
PPBBHHTT!

116
00:05:25,693 --> 00:05:29,029
THERE THEY ARE! GET BACK HERE,
YOU THIEVIN' VARMINTS!

117
00:05:29,062 --> 00:05:31,999
AWW, THAT WAS
SUCH A SWEET STORY.

118
00:05:32,032 --> 00:05:35,369
SWEET? TRY SAPPY.
[ YAWNS ]

119
00:05:35,403 --> 00:05:37,405
COME ON, WE'VE GOT TO FIND
RAINBOW DASH

120
00:05:37,438 --> 00:05:39,973
AND HEAR THE COOL WAY
TO GET A CUTIE MARK.

121
00:05:43,577 --> 00:05:44,912
AAH!
AAH!
AAH!

122
00:05:44,945 --> 00:05:46,614
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

123
00:05:46,647 --> 00:05:49,517
OHH!
OHH!
OHH!

124
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:51,652
Fluttershy: ALL RIGHT,
LITTLE ONES, THIS WAY.

125
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:53,053
THIS WAY.
[ QUACKING ]

126
00:05:53,086 --> 00:05:56,424
YOU REALLY SHOULD BE
MORE CAREFUL.

127
00:05:56,457 --> 00:05:57,925
SOMEPONY COULD GET HURT.

128
00:05:57,958 --> 00:05:59,927
WHY ARE YOU
IN SUCH A HURRY, ANYWAY?

129
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,762
WE'RE TRYING TO FIND
RAINBOW DASH

130
00:06:01,795 --> 00:06:03,597
SO WE CAN HEAR HOW
SHE EARNED HER CUTIE MARK.

131
00:06:03,631 --> 00:06:05,466
OH? THAT WOULD BE
INTERESTING.

132
00:06:05,499 --> 00:06:07,935
YOU KNOW, I WOULDN'T HAVE GOTTEN
MY CUTIE MARK

133
00:06:07,968 --> 00:06:09,169
IF IT WEREN'T FOR HER.

134
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:11,672
RAINBOW DASH?
REALLY?

135
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:15,609
OH, YES. IT ALL STARTED
AT SUMMER FLIGHT CAMP.

136
00:06:15,643 --> 00:06:18,412
YOU'D NEVER GUESS,
BUT WHEN I WAS LITTLE,

137
00:06:18,446 --> 00:06:22,416
I WAS VERY SHY
AND A VERY WEAK FLYER.

138
00:06:22,450 --> 00:06:23,617
OOH!

139
00:06:27,488 --> 00:06:28,489
OOH!

140
00:06:28,522 --> 00:06:31,191
AAH! YAH!

141
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:33,126
[ GASPS ]

142
00:06:37,164 --> 00:06:38,766
OH!

143
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:43,871
[ LAUGHS ]
NICE GOING, CLUTTERSHY.

144
00:06:43,904 --> 00:06:45,906
THEY OUGHT TO GROUND YOU
PERMANENTLY.

145
00:06:45,939 --> 00:06:48,976
HA! MY BABY BROTHER
CAN FLY BETTER THAN YOU.

146
00:06:49,009 --> 00:06:52,079
IT WAS THE MOST HUMILIATING
MOMENT OF MY LIFE.

147
00:06:52,112 --> 00:06:54,582
AND THEN,
OUT OF NOWHERE...

148
00:06:54,615 --> 00:06:56,750
[ ZOOM! ]

149
00:06:59,019 --> 00:07:00,454
LEAVE HER ALONE!

150
00:07:00,488 --> 00:07:03,757
OOH, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO,
RAINBOW CRASH?

151
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:06,594
KEEP MAKING FUN OF HER
AND FIND OUT!

152
00:07:06,627 --> 00:07:08,462
YOU THINK
YOU'RE SUCH A BIG SHOT?

153
00:07:08,496 --> 00:07:09,597
WHY DON'T YOU PROVE IT?

154
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:11,632
WHAT DO YOU
HAVE IN MIND?

155
00:07:15,102 --> 00:07:16,737
YOU'RE GOING DOWN.

156
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:18,138
IN HISTORY MAYBE.

157
00:07:18,171 --> 00:07:21,509
SEE YOU BOYS
AT THE FINISH LINE.

158
00:07:25,045 --> 00:07:26,814
[ ZIP! ]

159
00:07:26,847 --> 00:07:29,750
AH, AH, AAH!

160
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:32,185
YAAH!

161
00:07:34,922 --> 00:07:36,089
AH! AAH!

162
00:07:37,658 --> 00:07:43,130
[ SCREAMING ]

163
00:07:43,163 --> 00:07:44,965
HUH?

164
00:07:46,734 --> 00:07:50,270
I HAD NEVER SEEN
SUCH BEAUTIFUL CREATURES.

165
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:52,940
BUTTERFLIES DON'T FLY AS HIGH
AS MY CLOUD HOME,

166
00:07:52,973 --> 00:07:55,576
AND I HAD NEVER BEEN
NEAR THE GROUND BEFORE.

167
00:07:57,277 --> 00:08:02,583
* WHAT IS THIS PLACE
FILLED WITH SO MANY WONDERS *

168
00:08:02,616 --> 00:08:06,654
* CASTING ITS SPELL
THAT I AM NOW UNDER? *

169
00:08:06,687 --> 00:08:11,224
* SQUIRRELS IN THE TREES
AND THE CUTE LITTLE BUNNIES *

170
00:08:11,258 --> 00:08:16,263
* BIRDS FLYING FREE
AND BEES WITH THEIR HONEY *

171
00:08:16,296 --> 00:08:22,269
* HONE-E-E-E-Y

172
00:08:22,302 --> 00:08:25,072
* OH, WHAT A MAGICAL PLACE

173
00:08:25,105 --> 00:08:28,208
* AND I OWE IT ALL
TO THE PEGASUS RACE *

174
00:08:28,241 --> 00:08:31,144
* IF I KNEW THAT GROUND
HAD SO MUCH UP ITS SLEEVE *

175
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:34,247
* I'D HAVE COME HERE SOONER
AND NEVER LEAVE *

176
00:08:34,281 --> 00:08:43,156
* YES, I LOVE
EVERYTH-I-I-I-ING *

177
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:46,526
[ BOOM! ]

178
00:08:47,728 --> 00:08:49,029
[ CHITTERING ]

179
00:08:49,062 --> 00:08:50,230
[ RIBBITING ]

180
00:08:50,263 --> 00:08:51,632
[ CHIRPING ]

181
00:08:51,665 --> 00:08:54,768
[ SQUEALING ]

182
00:08:57,337 --> 00:08:59,039
Shh.

183
00:08:59,072 --> 00:09:00,874
IT'S OKAY.

184
00:09:03,944 --> 00:09:06,079
YOU CAN COME OUT.

185
00:09:08,849 --> 00:09:11,885
[ Warbly ]
EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

186
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:14,755
THERE'S NOTHING
TO BE AFRAID OF.
[ QUACKING ]

187
00:09:14,788 --> 00:09:17,625
[ ANIMALS CHATTERING ]

188
00:09:17,658 --> 00:09:19,993
SOMEHOW, I HAD THE ABILITY

189
00:09:20,027 --> 00:09:22,195
TO COMMUNICATE WITH THE ANIMALS
ON A DIFFERENT LEVEL.

190
00:09:22,229 --> 00:09:24,798
[ TWINKLE! ]

191
00:09:24,832 --> 00:09:27,635
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
WHAT HAPPENED TO RAINBOW DASH?

192
00:09:27,668 --> 00:09:28,802
WHAT ABOUT THE RACE?

193
00:09:28,836 --> 00:09:30,270
OH, WELL,
I WASN'T THERE,

194
00:09:30,303 --> 00:09:32,640
SO I DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED.

195
00:09:32,673 --> 00:09:35,175
COME ON, CRUSADERS.
WE'VE GOT TO FIND HER.

196
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:37,811
BESIDES, I CAN'T TAKE
ANY MORE SINGING.

197
00:09:37,845 --> 00:09:40,047
MAYBE MY SISTER KNOWS
WHERE SHE IS.

198
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,949
BYE, FLUTTERSHY!

199
00:09:41,982 --> 00:09:43,851
BYE, GIRLS.

200
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:50,223
HOW DID WE
GET ROPED INTO THIS?

201
00:09:50,257 --> 00:09:52,960
WE'LL NEVER HEAR
RAINBOW DASH'S STORY.

202
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:56,363
ARE YOU GIRLS STILL OBSESSING
OVER YOUR CUTIE MARKS?

203
00:09:56,396 --> 00:09:57,464
OF COURSE.

204
00:09:57,497 --> 00:10:00,801
MOST OF THE FILLIES AT SCHOOL
ALREADY HAVE THEIRS.

205
00:10:00,834 --> 00:10:01,969
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

206
00:10:02,002 --> 00:10:03,003
FOR THE LONGEST TIME,

207
00:10:03,036 --> 00:10:05,839
I COULDN'T FIGURE OUT
WHY I DIDN'T HAVE MINE.

208
00:10:05,873 --> 00:10:08,876
[ UP-TEMPO PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

209
00:10:14,214 --> 00:10:17,751
WELL DONE, RARITY.
YOUR COSTUMES ARE VERY NICE.

210
00:10:17,785 --> 00:10:20,721
NICE?!
THEY NEED TO BE SPECTACULAR!

211
00:10:20,754 --> 00:10:23,356
AND THE PERFORMANCE
IS TOMORROW!

212
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:26,727
I TRIED EVERY TRICK
I COULD THINK OF,

213
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:28,829
BUT NOTHING SEEMED TO WORK.

214
00:10:28,862 --> 00:10:32,099
THE COSTUMES JUST WEREN'T RIGHT,
AND THE PLAY OPENED THAT NIGHT.

215
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:35,736
MAYBE I'M NOT MEANT TO BE
A FASHIONISTA AFTER ALL.

216
00:10:35,769 --> 00:10:37,004
[ SPARKLE! ]

217
00:10:37,037 --> 00:10:38,438
AAH!

218
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:41,809
WHAT'S GOING ON?!

219
00:10:41,842 --> 00:10:44,812
I HAD NO IDEA
WHERE MY HORN WAS TAKING ME,

220
00:10:44,845 --> 00:10:47,414
BUT UNICORN MAGIC DOESN'T HAPPEN
WITHOUT A REASON.

221
00:10:47,447 --> 00:10:50,150
I KNEW THIS HAD TO DO
WITH MY LOVE OF FASHION --

222
00:10:50,183 --> 00:10:53,020
AND MAYBE EVEN MY CUTIE MARK!

223
00:10:53,053 --> 00:10:56,890
I KNEW THAT
THIS WAS MY DESTINY!

224
00:10:59,059 --> 00:11:00,427
A ROCK?!

225
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:02,029
THAT'S MY DESTINY?!

226
00:11:02,062 --> 00:11:04,064
WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM, HORN?!

227
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:07,000
I FOLLOWED YOU ALL THE WAY
OUT HERE FOR A ROCK?!

228
00:11:07,034 --> 00:11:09,169
HMPH!
DUMB ROCK!

229
00:11:09,202 --> 00:11:10,170
[ RUMBLE ]

230
00:11:10,203 --> 00:11:11,204
AAH!

231
00:11:16,143 --> 00:11:17,811
